    "body": "@paxthemax may have found the source of this. Copying his telegram update here:\r\n\r\nPavle Batuta, [13 May 2020 17:53:14]:\r\nHeads up everyone: I might have found some issues with improperly (redundantly loaded) typescript source maps when running tests. The usual way this would manifest is when an error pops up it will create a wrong line number off by an inconsistent amount.\r\n\r\nI've tracked down a situation when you would use:\r\n\r\n```ts\r\nimport { expect, use } fom chai;\r\nimport { solidtiy } from \"ethereum-waffle\";\r\n\r\nuse(solidity);\r\n...\r\nit(\"bla bla\", async function () {\r\n  expect(test.address).to.be.properAddress;\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhere solidity in question is a chai extender from waffle.\r\n\r\nWhen the chai.use call is removed, the source map seems to be exactly right.",
